# Cursor Layout Rules — Cafe Delight Admin Panel UI

## 0) Prime UI Directive
- Follow the generated layout strictly:
  - Left dark sidebar
  - Top header bar
  - Clean white content area
  - Card-based dashboard
- Do NOT redesign structure unless explicitly instructed.
- Keep layout consistent across ALL admin pages.

---

## 1) Layout Structure Rules

### Sidebar (Left Navigation)
- Fixed vertical sidebar.
- Dark background.
- Contains:
  - Logo / Brand name (Cafe Delight Admin)
  - Dashboard
  - Categories
  - Menu Items
  - Offers
  - Orders
- Icons required for each menu item.
- Active menu item must be visually highlighted.
- Sidebar width must remain consistent across pages.

### Top Header Bar
- Light background.
- Right side:
  - Admin avatar
  - Dropdown (Profile / Logout)
- Page title displayed clearly below header.
- No clutter in header.

### Content Area
- White background.
- Consistent padding (minimum 24px).
- Use card components for:
  - Stats
  - Tables
  - Forms
- Do not mix too many visual styles.

---

## 2) Dashboard Rules

### Stat Cards
- Show:
  - New Orders
  - Preparing
  - Ready
  - Total Sales
- Each card:
  - Has icon
  - Colored background
  - Large number
  - Clear label
- Cards must align in one row (responsive grid).

### Orders Table
- Clean table with:
  - Order ID
  - Customer
  - Status badge
  - Total
- Status must use colored badges:
  - received → gray
  - preparing → blue
  - ready → orange
  - delivered → green
  - cancelled → red

---

## 3) Table Rules (Menu / Orders / Offers)

- Tables must be:
  - Searchable
  - Sortable
  - Filterable
- Use:
  - Status filters
  - Category filters
  - Availability filters
- Actions column must include:
  - Edit
  - View (if needed)
  - Update Status (Orders)
- Use toggle switches for:
  - Availability
  - Featured
- Image thumbnail must be small and aligned left.

---

## 4) Form Rules (Create / Edit Pages)

### Structure
- Use sections:
  - Basic Info
  - Pricing
  - Status
  - Media
- Two-column layout when possible.
- Labels above inputs.
- Required fields clearly marked.

### Inputs
- Text inputs for name/price.
- Select dropdowns for:
  - Category
  - Offer type
  - Offer scope
- Toggle switches for booleans.
- Date pickers for offer schedule.
- Image upload preview required.

### Buttons
- Primary button: Blue ("Save")
- Secondary button: Gray ("Cancel")
- Buttons aligned bottom-right.

---

## 5) Order Management UI Rules

- Must have tab filters:
  - All
  - Preparing
  - Ready
  - Delivered
- Status badge colors must remain consistent everywhere.
- Update status must be:
  - Dropdown action
  - Or modal confirmation
- Provide Print button on order detail page.

---

## 6) Spacing & Typography Rules

- Use consistent spacing scale.
- Headings:
  - Page Title: Large bold
  - Section Title: Medium bold
- Tables:
  - Medium row height
  - Clean separators
- No crowded UI.

---

## 7) Consistency Rules

- Same button style everywhere.
- Same badge colors everywhere.
- Same toggle style everywhere.
- Same card radius everywhere.
- No inline custom styles unless necessary.

---

## 8) UX Quality Rules

- No broken alignment.
- No overflowing content.
- All forms must show validation errors clearly.
- No empty state without message:
  - "No orders yet"
  - "No menu items added"

---

## 9) Responsive Rules

- Sidebar collapses on small screens.
- Tables scroll horizontally on mobile.
- Cards stack vertically on small screens.
- Forms switch to single column on mobile.

---

## 10) Definition of Done (UI)

Admin UI is complete only if:
- All pages follow the same layout pattern.
- Colors and spacing are consistent.
- No UI element looks default or unfinished.
- Status badges and toggles behave correctly.
